However, you can help us reach the TWENTY20 match campaign's $20,000 goal, which will set off an additional $20,000 in donations from a very special group of donors listed on the virtual gala event page. We're 87% of the way there! Setahun dua rasa ok untuk travel jauh sbb mungkin masa tu masih belum ada anak or anak masih kecil. 

Cuba imagine bila anak dah faham dan sekolah. Terpaksa korban masa bersama anak atas jalan raya ditemani jam. Sampai rumah dah pukul 9 malam. Siap diner je dah pukul 10-11mlm, anak pun dah nak tido. Alangkah baiknya kalau sempat teman main2 dengan anak or assist diaorg buat homework. Masa lihat merek membesar tak bole beli semula. 

Masatu pasti menyesal sbb x beli property dekat bandar ?. Nak jual property yg tinggal sekrang murah sangat plus susah nak dpt buyer sbb less demand. What to do now,terpaksalah bekorban tinggal juga.

Jangan jadi penting diri seperti story di atas. Sis bole bantu miliki property below market value dalam bandar yang matured.

Foam rolling is a self-myofascial release (SMR) technique. It can help relieve muscle tightness, soreness, and inflammation, and increase your joint range of motion.  Today, my lower back was really tight and foam rolling almost helped immediately. 

Foam rolling can be an effective tool to add to your warm-up or cooldown, before and after exercise. And the benefits of foam rolling may vary from person to person. 

Doctors orders: If you don't own one, I advise that you consider purchasing one to help ease muscle pain, increase range of motion, reduce appearance of cellulite, and to relieve back pain.

Sharing a sneak-peek of the new logo - part of Smart Heart 2.0. We've been hard at work on the new version of the game, making sure to keep emotional intelligence at its core.

Emotional expression skills and the ability to understand other people's emotions are crucial for a balanced and successful life. Not everyone is equally good at appropriate emotional expression, but it is certainly something that can be learned. While some children may be good at expressing their needs and wants clearly, the majority of kids (and many adults) struggle with this.

Smart Heart creates a platform for children to learn appropriate emotional expression. The 'I feel...when...' deck of cards are geared at teaching this important life skill - in the game - children are encouraged to pick a feelings card and share what they feel, and when they feel that way: e.g. "I feel...frustrated when... I can't get to the next level in my game"

Do you feel you're able to identify the full range of emotions you have in a day? How has not being aware of your emotions led to a behavior you later regret? Do you feel you miss opportunities because you're not able to pick up on other people's emotions? #ConsciousParent
